SIMPLE: waggish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waggish
<hw>Wag"gish</hw> <pr>(-g⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Like a wag; mischievous in sport; roguish in merriment or good
humor; frolicsome.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A company of <xex>waggish</xex>
boys.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Done, made, or laid in waggery or for sport;
sportive; humorous; <as>as, a <ex>waggish</ex> trick</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wag"gish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wag"gish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waggle</ent>⟦br⟧
